[Teeth of Shartan, landslide]
The old road is buried here beneath a massive pile of rocks and rubble,
dramatic evidence of a recent landslide. A wide swath has been scraped bare of
soil and trees nearly to the peak of the western ridge. Ancient uquarts, their
limbless trunks larger around than the stoutest innkeeper, lay scattered about
like straw cast from a child's hand. Atop the rubble, a glorious array of
wildflowers bloom in the newly open space.
You see an ursine and an ursine. 
Obvious exits: south.
