[Teeth of Shartan, uquart grove]
Two trails intersect at a shallow angle here, making a four way intersection
among the uquart. A few small annual plants poke up through the carpet of
needles that cover the ground, grasping for what little sunlight filters down
through the dense needles of the uquart. Bright splotches of crimson dye mark
the trees along a narrow trail to the northeast, but the main road clearly
extends to the north and south from here. To the southwest, only ruffled
needles mark the path.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: north, south, northeast, southwest.
