[Teeth of Shartan, uquart grove]
The air here is permeated with the rich smell of uquart sap from the trees of
this peaceful grove. Few of the sun's rays penetrate the canopy of needles
overhead, so the grove is cool and dark even on the brightest of summer days. A
few of the trees have tufts of color at the end of their needled branches, the
uquart's only concession to the need to reproduce. A great arcing rocky ridge
surrounds the grove to the south and west, blocking any further travel in those
directions.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: east, northeast.
