[Teeth of Shartan, uquart grove]
The ridge to the west opens into a wide bowl here, with enough standing water
and level terrain to support a large grove of uquart trees. Their slender
needles carpet the path here, masking even the sound of the swiftly flowing
water under the gentle rush of wind through the branches overhead. A few small
rodents scurry about in the needles, looking for the swollen seed pods of the
uquart. The grove extends a short distance to the west from here.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: north, west, southeast.
