DEAD> 
Wolfbane goes southeast.
DEAD> 
Wolfbane carries you.
[Teeth of Shartan, valley]
The gentle curve of the mountain stream has obscured the opening in the valley
behind the mountains to the south, increasing the feeling of closeness. In
every direction lie rocky ridges and lofty peaks. Their summits still hold
small caps of snow even this late in the year. Further down the slope, grasses
and wildflowers have decorated the mountainsides with a rich tapestry of
colors. Despite their serenity, the mountains seem to press downward with
tremendous force.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: south, northwest.
DEAD> 
Wolfbane goes south.
DEAD> 
Wolfbane carries you.
[Teeth of Shartan, valley]
Several large boulders are strewn about the valley floor here, no doubt having
rolled from the fractured peaks of the mountains above. Two particularly
massive boulders have come to rest in midstream, channelling the flow of water
between them into a roaring, frothing chute.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: north, south.
DEAD> 
Wolfbane climbs a massive boulder.
DEAD> 
Wolfbane carries you.
[Teeth of Shartan, atop a boulder]
This large boulder stands partway out into the rapidly flowing waters of the
mountian stream. A second boulder, nearly as large as this one, stands on the
opposite bank of the stream. A healthy group of mosses and lichens thrives on
the top of the boulder in the cool, moist spray from from the swift water
flowing below.  An agile person could probably jump across the stream here to
the other boulder.
You see Wolfbane. 
Obvious exits: down.
