[Commerce Street]
A large stone building with a wooden door, the Physician's Guild, shoulders
aside the smaller structures of the Guild of Carpenters and the Ropers' Guild.
People of all stations enter the guilds seeking services for themselves or
their organizations.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: east, southwest.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Commerce Street]
Guilds of every variety cram the buildings of Commerce Street. The Guild of
Exterminators, of Entertainers and Artists, House Builders, Coopers,
Apothecaries, Smiths, Mourners, Masons and dozens of others: each has a place.
A tall stone building stands out from the crowd because bright multi-colored
woven tapestries flank the sides its entrance, a wooden door carved with some
words.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: west, northeast.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes northeast.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Commerce Street]
Commerce plunges deeper into the warehouse and guild district to the southwest.
On the northwest side of the street the aging facade of the Adventurers' Guild
promises the young at heart rewards for their generous spirit. A wooden door
hangs almost off its hinges from the rickety building. Across the street you
can see the shattered opening that leads into a small brick building.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: northeast, southwest.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes northeast.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Main Street & Pleasant & Commerce]
This intersection forms a hub. Main Street comes to an end, and Pleasant and
Commerce both terminate or begin here, depending on how you look at it. The
moving crowds are split between banged up and nicked adventurers heading for
the Physicians' Guild, and merchants and craftsmen delivering their work for
sale at the bazaar.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: south, east, southwest.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Main Street & Elm]
Main Street runs east and west, and Elm Street goes north from here. On the
south side of Main, an ancient tower reaches into the lowering sky like a
needle. It is the Tower of Silver Arcana, headquarters for the order of the
same name. In its side, an opening with a plaque affixed over it allows entry.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: north, east, west.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Main Street]
The majestic building in front of you houses City Hall. A stone stairway
curves up to its entrance between two venerable statues, one marble and
one bronze. A ceremonial spray of leafless goldvine stands at the base
of each one.  A small building has been erected here recently, serving as
a guardpost that's manned continuously.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: east, west.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Main Street]
Large buildings, featureless in the gray light, loom around you here midway
between the bazaar and Fayd's downtown district. People crowd past you on
important business, and you feel small and insignificant among so many in such
a hurry.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: east, west.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Main Street]
Distant cries of hawkers tell you that the bazaar lies east of here. Heading
west leads you deeper into the city. Trash from an upturned refuse bin mixes
with dead leaves next to the curb.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: east, west.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Bazaar West]
The Armorer's Guild buys a surprising variety of old and damaged weapons from
local adventurers and melts them down to make the new weaponry and armor on
display. Would be owners may examine the manuscript on the table to see what
new equipment can be afforded. Main Street continues west behind the stalls.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northeast, southeast.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Bazaar Center]
There is a chill to the air blowing in from the eastern wastes here, yet the
excitment of the bazaar with its tumult keeps the cold from your spirit if not
your body. The center of the bazaar overwhelms your senses with the smell and
sizzle of roast 
mutton, its cries of hawkers and cajoling merchants. Jugglers, minstrels, and
street dancers a-whirl to stay warm amuse the crowds gathered near a large
marble fountain.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. A wooden bin and a newsboard are here.
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northeast, northwest, southeast,
southwest.
J> 
Wolfbane's group goes east.
J> 
You follow Wolfbane.
[Bazaar East]
Here at the eastern edge of the bazaar, street merchants of wares both mundane
and fantastic set up their booths daily to catch your eye. From The Sojourner's
Hospice, a run-down yet cozy inn on the corner, comes singing and the smell of
spiced wine. A door with a holly wreath in its center leads in.
You see Madrina, Wolfbane and Delight. 
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northwest, southwest.
