[Saloon, private booth]
The booth has comfortable seats, slightly upholstered, surrounding a square
table of medium size. On the table is a centerpiece consisting of a glass
bubble with an open top, a candle burning merrily within it to throw light,
dancing and flickering, in every direction.
Obvious exits: out.
It is Farnum 9, 1033 (Year of the Wyrm).
It is early morning.
The Great Moon is crescent waning and Phulcrus is crescent waxing.
The curtain falls back into place as Taliesin enters the booth.
> out
.
[Saloon]
This good-sized barroom is filled with the sounds of laughter and clinking
glasses produced by the many patrons who occupy its round wooden tables and
lean against the impressive, stained oak bar. The wall behind the bar is
mostly occupied by a large, silvered mirror which seems to double the size
of the room. A portrait hangs just between the mirror and a narrow wooden
stairway. Also at the back of the room, on the east and west walls, a door
and an archway face each other along the length of the bar, each made from
the same type of fine, polished oak as the bar, the stairway and the tables.
A porcelain flask is here.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> [Bazaar Southeast]
This corner of the bazaar has been the focus of an urban renewal project
for over a year, now, and it is really shaping up nicely. A newly painted
arch with a bronze plaque leads into a courtyard to the east, while to the
south a pair of wooden doors lead into a building overlooking the bazaar.
Obvious exits: north, west, northwest.
> 
